# GoArrive — Cursor Rules

## Project
GoArrive is an online fitness coaching platform. React Native + Expo + Expo Router + Firebase. Single codebase for web, iOS, Android. Multi-tenant, three roles: platformAdmin, coach, member.

## Stack
- React Native + Expo (web, iOS, Android)
- Expo Router (file-based routing)
- TypeScript (strict mode)
- Cloud Firestore (40+ collections)
- Firebase Auth (custom claims)
- Firebase Cloud Functions Gen 2 (52+ functions)
- Stripe Connect, Zoom API, Google Calendar API
- NO MySQL, TiDB, Drizzle, Fastify, S3

## Critical Auth Pattern
Always use `effectiveUid` or `claims.coachId` from `useAuth()` — never `user.uid` directly.
This breaks admin impersonation if violated.
All coach-scoped queries: `where('coachId', '==', coachId)`.

## Code Style
- camelCase everywhere: Firestore docs, TS interfaces, props, state
- Product language: "coach" not trainer, "member" not client, "movement" not exercise, "Command Center" not dashboard
- FlatList for lists > 500 items
- thumbnailUrl for initial media loads
- Soft deletes via isArchived flag, never hard deletes

## Three Roles Only
platformAdmin, coach, member. No CoachAssistant, no Encourager, no fourth role.

## Build Tab
Workout creation starts on a blank block canvas, NOT a metadata form.
Movements use 4:5 aspect ratio.
The Build tab is a unified workspace replacing separate Workouts and Movements tabs.

## Testing
- Vitest for logic: `cd apps/goarrive && npm run test:vitest`
- Playwright for E2E: `npm run test:e2e`
- Deploy to staging first: `cd apps/goarrive && npm run deploy:staging`

## Do Not Build
MySQL, TiDB, Drizzle, S3, Fastify, JotForm, Calendly, Zoom Embedded SDK, white-label, custom domains, additional roles.

## Key Files
- apps/goarrive/lib/AuthContext.tsx — Auth + admin impersonation
- apps/goarrive/app/(app)/build.tsx — Unified Build workspace
- functions/src/index.ts — 52+ Cloud Functions
- .claude/ — Full knowledge base (17 detailed docs)
